            . I am a constable of Portsoken Ward. On the evening of the 7th of October, about eight o'clock, I was in <placeName id="t18341016-66-crimeloc370">Aldgate</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18341016-66-crimeloc370" type="placeName" value="Aldgate"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18341016-66-crimeloc370" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18341016-66-off368 t18341016-66-crimeloc370"></join>, and saw the prisoner and another following two gentlemen - they came towards me - I saw the prisoner lift Mr. Josiah Walker's coat tail up, and take something out of his pocket - I immediately caught hold of him, and took this handkerchief from his hand.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18341016-66-person712">
                  JOSIAH 
                  WALKER
               <interp inst="t18341016-66-person712" type="surname" value="WALKER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18341016-66-person712" type="given" value="JOSIAH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18341016-66-person712" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t18341016-66-viclabel371" type="occupation">woollen-draper</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18341016-66-victim710 t18341016-66-viclabel371"></join>, and live in Mitre-street, Aldgate. On the night in question, Morgan called my attention, and I missed a white cambric handkerchief, which he produced - it is my property - I had it quite safe just before the alarm was given.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was walking along, and saw a young man run across the road - I saw the handkerchief lay on the ground - the gentleman came and took me - he took the handkerchief from the ground, and called the prosecutor back.</p>
               <p>
            
